cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CY

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques to predict the gender of Indonesian names. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and ML. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, specifically Long-Short Term Memory (LSTM), which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also compares its results with conventional ML algorithms, which fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with cultural aspects of Indonesian names, which could fall under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
